name: Aphrodite Canyon
description:
Introduction

completed 2-11-16 by Scott Swaney and Aysel Gezik. looking or new canyons. The upper two drops are together and done in two stages. The overall wall drop here is 400'to 500' high. Very spectacular drop and continues down into a short cool narrow section. The upper 330' rappel is also over a large overhanging section, making it a very airy drop.

Background

completed 2-11-16 by Scott Swaney And Aysel Gezik. On an exploratory mission for more new canyons. We did find evidence that someone had been in a portion of this canyon before. On our approach hike up, there were places that someone could drop into the canyon early and do the lower drops
